Description: Rim and neck sherd of Corinthian pottery transport amphora; echinus rim with two ridges below; fine yellow-cream clay; dipinto inscription on neck.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIV, no. 656)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 673, no. 317)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GB.313)
